cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.CV, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the use of quality-diversity algorithms in artificial intelligence for games, specifically in procedural content generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of behavior metrics, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses game playing, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT), and the use of computer vision techniques for generating game content (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for human-AI interaction, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR).
